The paper deals with the problem of single image super-resolution, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves neural texture transfer, which is a technique that falls under the category of generative models (cs.MM). The paper also presents an end-to-end deep model, which involves training a neural network, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves building a benchmark dataset, which is a task related to graphics (cs.GR).
